	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've made the following observations with this weapon's beserker strength feature:<BR>
<BR>
1) I gained 19 strength and only lost 10 agility.  perhaps these numbers are affected by stats?<BR>
<BR>
2) When it happens is entirely random<BR>
<BR>
3) The duration is like an affect spell.  If you are not in a fight it will stay for quite a long time, then the affect will start blinking and it will turn off.<BR>
<BR>
4) During battle it suddenly turns off, often just a few seconds after turning on.  There are 2 possible reasons for this:<BR>
<BR>
  A) Each time the enemy hits they do a save vs magic and if they get the roll it dispells the affect<BR>
<BR>
  B) If the enemy's attack value for a hit is very high (they would have gotten a really good hit off) then it dispells the affect.  This seems likely since hard hitting mobs dispell it faster and because it seems it always wears off at the same time a really strong hit comes in.<BR>
<BR>
For those that aren't sure I have verified that the beserker strength does in fact make you invulnerable to non-magic attacks, increase your strength, and decrease your agility but is affected by factors listed above.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
